  <h1>5S Methodology for Chemical Plants: A Guide to Organization and Efficiency</h1>
  <p>Welcome! This webpage is your one-stop resource for learning about the 5S methodology and its application within chemical plants.</p>

  <h2>What is 5S?</h2>
  <p>The 5S methodology is a workplace organization system originating in Japan. It focuses on five key principles, each starting with the letter "S":</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Sort (Seiri): Eliminate unnecessary items from the workplace.</li>
    <li>Set in Order (Seiton): Arrange necessary items in a designated and labeled location for easy retrieval.</li>
    <li>Shine (Seiso): Maintain a clean and hygienic work environment.</li>
    <li>Standardize (Seiketsu): Establish consistent practices to ensure ongoing organization and cleanliness.</li>
    <li>Sustain (Shitsuke): Foster a culture of continuous improvement and adherence to 5S principles.</li>
  </ul>

